cs.RO, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper focuses on integrating open-source software components from computational neuroscience and robotics to evaluate the validity of biologically-plausible plasticity models in closed-loop robotics environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of a reward-learning rule based on synaptic sampling on two visuomotor tasks, indicating a potential connection to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the visuomotor tasks involve visual perception, suggesting a possible connection to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
